Cell B13 currently holds a SUMIF formula that sums values in column B where column I contains the text in A13.  
The task is to modify this formula so that it also excludes any rows where column I contains any numeric characters.  

We will replace the formula in B13 with a SUMPRODUCT formula that:
1. Checks that column I contains the substring from A13 (`ISNUMBER(SEARCH(A13, I_range))`).
2. Ensures column I does **not** contain any digit 0‑9 (`ISERROR(SEARCH(digit, I_range))` for each digit).
3. Multiplies the boolean masks and multiplies by the corresponding values in column B, then sums the result.

The new formula will be written directly into cell B13, preserving the rest of the sheet unchanged.

After updating, we will save the workbook to the output directory, recalculate formulas, and verify that B13 now contains a non‑error value.
Code:
```repl
import pathlib, openpyxl
from openpyxl.utils import column_index_from_string

# Paths
input_path = pathlib.Path("/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_42181_init.xlsx")
output_dir = pathlib.Path("/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/")
output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
output_path = output_dir / "1_42181_init.xlsx"

# Load workbook (keep formulas)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb.active  # only one sheet

# Define ranges (rows 4-10 as in original formula)
row_start = 4
row_end = 10
b_range = f"$B${row_start}:$B${row_end}"
i_range = f"$I${row_start}:$I${row_end}"

# Build SUMPRODUCT formula
# Part 1: column I contains A13
contains_text = f'ISNUMBER(SEARCH(A13,{i_range}))'

# Part 2: column I does NOT contain any digit 0-9
digits = [str(d) for d in range(10)]
no_digit_parts = [f'ISERROR(SEARCH("{d}",{i_range}))' for d in digits]
no_digit = "*".join(no_digit_parts)

# Combine into SUMPRODUCT
new_formula = f'=SUMPRODUCT(({contains_text})*({no_digit})*({b_range}))'

# Write formula into B13
ws["B13"].value = new_formula

# Save workbook
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas
await recalculate(str(output_path))

# Verify B13 value after recalculation
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
val = wb_check.active["B13"].value
print("B13 after recalculation:", val)
